The paper deals with the complexity of integer linear programming problems, which are often studied in the context of algorithms and computational complexity. The paper discusses the existence of polynomial kernels for these problems, which is a topic that falls under the category of parameterized complexity. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are all likely categories. Additionally, the paper involves some geometric and graph-theoretic arguments, which suggest that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also possible categories.
